      nc0's Web Toolkit (often abbreviated as nWT) is a tool box for
   developers and designers to create and iterate on hypertext documents
   quickly, without compromising on responsivness and elegance.
   Composed of libraries and guides for HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and more,
   nWT is perfectly suited for prototyping as well as production usage in
   all modern browsers (and sometimes even Internet Explorer).

   Each library and guide is self-contained in its own file, feel free to
   explore them for documentation and more:

   (1) Fluid Layout (fl.css) is a functional CSS library providing a
       flexible, responsive, and intuitive layout system for CSS.


   Documentation and distribution of nWT is also available on-line at
   https://nc0.fr/web.

   You may clone this repository using Git:

       git clone https://git.puffer.fish/nico/web.git

   (a mirror of which is also available on GitHub at
   https://github.com/ncs-pl/web.git, but it might not be in sync).

   Discussions, development, and announcements related to nWT are active
   on the <nwt@puffer.fish> mailing list.

   The nWT project is distributed for free and without any warranty.
   Study the COPYRIGHT file for the entire distribution terms.

